race.comment: SIR LEAPALOT (2) just failed to meet market expectations first-up when charging home to miss by a head. Sure to have come on from that and should settle much closer this time. Claimer sticks to keep him in well at the weights. Gets his chance to break a long run of outs. ZUETORO (3) was a determined winner two back when getting the bob and backed it up with another brave effort last time. Needs some luck from the draw but has found form and warrants strong consideration. AMBELLO (4) doesn't win often but thrives at this track and trip. Reunites with Murtagh, who knows him well. Should be competitive. LAKE AGAWAM (10) caught the eye two back when flashing home to miss narrowly at Balaklava. Not as effective last time but remains worth keeping in mind.
